headline: Equifax, TransUnion stocks fall after FHFA criticism on pricing
summary: Investing.com -- Equifax (NYSE:EFX) stock fell 2.3% and TransUnion (NYSE:TRU) stock dropped 2.5% after Federal Housing Finance Agency Director Bill Pulte criticized the credit reporting companies’ pricing practices.
